<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><input type="hidden" name="PHPSESSID" value="c7fd488171dcc9f20d438c7ec38b96d2" /><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/vs/articles/index.php'>Marvel VS</option><option value='/heroclix/articles/articles.php'>HeroClix</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magic/articles/articles.php'>Video Games and Movies</option><option value='/wars/articles/articles.php'>Wizards Minis</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> LOTR Q&A Rulings from 06/03/04<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.86)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=617'>Enrique "Max of Tat" Huerta</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=617&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> June 17, 2004</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> Not for review.<br />
Originally posted on 06/03/04.<br />
===============================<br />
<br />
Hello All!!<br />
<br />
   Well, Reflections is out and it sounds like it&#39;s having an immediate impact on the tournament scene. Even my beloved Dwarves are seeing play. And dare I say they might be Tier 1! Okay, okay Tier 1.5. (=<br />
<br />
   No CRD update this month again, but that doesn&#39;t seem to be a problem as there were lots of questions this update. And for the first time since I started doing this, I have finally been given a question I can not answer. (But to be fair, I&#39;d like to think it&#39;s because there is not answer.) You decide...<br />
<br />
- Enrique<br />
<br />
<h3>Questions about Card Rulings:</h3><br />
<b>i have a question about eregion trails. am i able to play it during the manuver and make the minion roaming during the skirmish and still make that minion strength -3? EXAMPLE: i play eregion trails have 2 ancient roads out i then assign the minions to all (gondor) ranger companions, or would they have to roaming during the manuver for me to use this ability? or does it last until the skirmish phase? [the easterling] </b><br />
<br />
<b>I was told to ask you about any questions I had on rules pretaining to the LoTR game. <br />
<br />
If you play Eregion&#39;s Trials, when no minions are roaming, <br />
Then during the skirmish phase, you have Gaondorian Rangers/Ancient Roads etc. to make them roaming, <br />
Do they get -3 strength, or do they have to be roaming during the manuever phase for this to work?[Tsuchi]</b><br />
<br />
A: No.<br />
<br />
Because of the &quot;snapshot&quot; rule, Eregion&#39;s Trials only affects minions that are roaming when it&#39;s played. That means that if non-roaming minions later become roaming, they are still unaffected by the event becuase they were not roaming when the event was played. And by the same token, roaming minions that later become non-roaming, would still remain affected by the event because they were roaming when the event was played.<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Hi Enrique. I know this isn&#39;t exactly a brainbuster, but can Narsil be played with Shards of Narsil out? They are both unique, and I don&#39;t believe so, but I&#39;ve seen a few deck posts with both in. Thanks.[OrangeJedi]</b> <br />
<br />
A: Yes.<br />
<br />
For game purposes Narsil, The Shards of Narsil, and even Anduril are all different &quot;personas&quot; because they all have different titles. In other words, all three can be in play at once with no restrictions or problems. <br />
<br />
This is just one of those instances when the game differs from the story. <br />
<br />
<b>i have questions regarding cards like ancient blade and sauramons staff. Cards such as ancient blade say that each minion gaines a line of text, while sauramons staff allows you to ignore the first line of text on sauramon. My question is can the cards such as ancient blade be used to prevent the ability granted by sauramons staff. Who decides, if anyone, where the extra line of text gets placed. Thanks. [faceface] </b><br />
<br />
A: Cards like Ancient Blade do not &quot;prevent&quot; the ability granted by Saruman&#39;s Staff.<br />
<br />
Cards like Ancient Blade grant minions a special ability, but they don&#39;t necessarily add game text to those minions. So Saruman&#39;s Staff would still ignore the first line of game text printed on the Saruman card.<br />
<br />
<b>If i have a black sails of umbar in play with 5 tokens,can i play castamir by dicarding the sails and play two twilight tokens or do i need to have 7 token on sail to play him [Black raider]</b><br />
<br />
A: You can play Castamir for only 2 twilight.<br />
<br />
Black Sails of Umbar lets you play any Corsair from your discard pile. The corsair does not have to cost same number of tokens you removed from the possession. (It would say something like &quot;who&#39;s twilight cost is X, where X = the number of tokens removed.&quot;) Instead the twilight cost of the minion played is cheaper because of the number of tokens you removed.<br />
<br />
Note: You cannot remove 5 tokens to play a 4-cost Corsair and add 1 twilight token.<br />
<br />
<b>Here&#39;s my question... the Moria event card, Power and Terror it says to &quot;Reveal any number of moria Orcs from your hand to play the Balrog. Its twilight cost is -2 for each Orc revealed.&quot; I just need to know if it means you have to play the Balrog from hand, draw deck, or discard pile. It doesn&#39;t specify. Thanks man. [The Fry] </b><br />
<br />
A: The Balrog would have to be from hand.<br />
<br />
Unless specified otherwise, all cards are played from hand. Compared, for example, to the Bridge of Khazad-dum which allows you to play the Balrog from either your hand or your draw deck.<br />
<br />
<b>1. Still Far Ahead 8U29 - (a) If I spot Smeagol and play SFA, but my next site is already in place (because my opponent moved first causing me to play that site from my adventure deck) does the first sentence of SFA text have any effect? Does the second sentence still apply to reduce the shadow number of the site by 1? (b) Can I play SFA even if I cannot spot Smeagol and apply the second sentence of the text to reduce the shadow number of the site by 1? 2. Grond 8R103 - May X be zero? (So that, for example, I can remove any zero cost FP card without having to remove any tokens from Grond provided I discard a Sauron minion or Grond itself) Thanks for your help. Peter Cornell, Cambridge, England [Voltor] </b><br />
<br />
A: 1.(a)Yes. No. (b)No.   2. Yes.<br />
<br />
As long as you meet the requirements and pay the costs, you may play an action. You carry out as much of the effect as possible and ignore the rest. If your site is already out, you&#39;d ignore the effect of having to play your next site. Eventhough you didn&#39;t play your site again, you&#39;d still be able to carry our the effect of making the next site -1. But if you can not meet all the requirements (like spotting Smeagol) then you may not play the action. And if you don&#39;t play the action, then you obviously can&#39;t get the effects.<br />
<br />
Yes, X may equal 0. As long as you discard a [Sauron] minion or Grond you may remove 0 tokens to discard a card with 0 twilight cost.<br />
<br />
<h3>Questions about Game/Tournament Rulings:</h3><br />
<b>If someone bears the One Ring (which isn&#39;t an artifact nor a possesion), can they also bear an ring as an artifact? This was never a problem because there are no hobbit rings, but now, let&#39;s say, Gimli is the ring bearer. Can he also bear the Ring of Guile or another dwarven ring or does The One Ring prevent him from bearing another ring because of the one type of possesion rule? Thanks, Alex [blueraider0]</b><br />
<br />
A: Yes.<br />
<br />
The restriction in the rules to bearing more than one item of the same class only applies to possessions and artifacts. So even though the One Ring is a &quot;Ring&quot;, it is not a possession nor artifact, so it does not limit the Ring-bearer for wearing another &quot;Ring&quot; possession or artifact (but not both!).<br />
<br />
<b>Your #2 fan here again. Thanks for answering my questions about the black flail and black breath. Thanks for answering my question about Pippin WoBaS too. My new question is about assignment. Can the shadow player choose to leave their minions unassigned if the free peoples doesn&#39;t assign them? Ex 1: Bill ferny is out at site 7 (regroup spot 6 companions and your minion to make them move again) and wherever you put ferny he will die so the shadow player CAN THEY LEAVE THEM UNASSIGNED to make them move again? Ex 2: Site 9 with lone frodo and 0 burdens the free peoples player has 4 paths in hand and the shadow player knowing this plays 2 trolls. The shadow player leaves one troll assigned to frodo and the other unassigned so that the FP player must burn the paths during the first skirmish and then the 2nd troll would kill frodo in the fierce. Can the shadow player leave minions unassigned? My friend says this topic isn&#39;t really covered in the rulebook thanks. [Christian Na] </b><br />
<br />
A: Yes.<br />
<br />
All assignment actions are optional. If the Free Peoples Player does not assign a minion, either by choice or otherwise, the Shadow player may still decide to not assign the unassigned minions. The rulebook entry you&#39;re looking for is on page 15 of the Comprehensive Rulebook 3.0. &quot;When you have informed the Shadow players that you are done making assignments, they may assign any unassigned minions to any companions...&quot;. The key word is &quot;may&quot;. The Shadow player does not have to assigned the minions that were unassigned.<br />
<br />
<b>Hi, Enrique. This is my cuestion: I have a dunland minion with vitality 2 and a hides on the table (I’ve not more pull). My opponent (in maniober actions) plays Terrible and Evil and he wants exerts Gandalf 3 times to wound my minion 3 times (2 of the vitality and one more becouse he gives me 3 of pull and I can use the hides). Can he does it? I thought that the exert limit of this card was the minion vitality but reading the card it has not limit. If he pays the cost (3 of pull and X exerts on Gandalf) he has the effects. Thanks [Raúl Rodríguez] </b><br />
<br />
A: Yes.<br />
<br />
As long as you meet the requirements and pay the costs, you may play an action. You carry out as much of the effect as possible and ignore the rest. So if the FPP wants to exert Gandalf more times then the minion has vitality, that is fine. If the minion is killed before all the wounds are placed the placement of the remaining wounds would be ignored. And if you do discard Hides to prevent a wound, you&#39;d still have to take the other two wounds.<br />
<br />
However! (= You do not have to use Hides, in which case you can be satisfied in knowing that Gandalf exerted more times than was necessary and that hopefully you&#39;d be able to take advantage of your opponent&#39;s mistake further along in the game.<br />
<br />
However! However! (= Because your opponent has to meet the requirements and pay the costs of the event before  the effects can happen, your opponent will have to add 3 twilight to the pool in order to play Terrible and Evil. This 3 twilight is immediately available to you to use for Hides to prevent a wound. So if you wished, you could remove 2 to prevent 1 wound, discard Hides to prevent another wound, and place the last wound on your minion who would still be alive. So it would be possible to take advantage of your opponent&#39;s mistake at this site! <br />
<br />
<b>Do &#39;resistance adding&#39; cards add resistance to my ringbearer when that card is not active? What about my ringbearer&#39;s text? For example, during my opponents turn, my scroll of isildur is not active. Do I gain a resistance bonus from it? Or how about Galadriel&#39;s resistance bonus text, or Gimli&#39;s resistance bonus text. Are those still &#39;kicking in&#39; when my ringbearer is not active? If yes to the above, what about Aggression and Gimli the ringbearer, which only provide a damage bonus (and therefore, resistance bonus) when i have initiative? (if no to the above, this question is moot). This could be very important when considering timed win tiebreakers, since if the last turn is my opponents turn and these cards don&#39;t count I might even have NEGATIVE resistance left! [Alan Sagan] </b><br />
<br />
A: Your Fellowship cards are not active during your opponent&#39;s turn.<br />
<br />
Now this is definiately a tricky question and one that has many impacts on the game. First off let me clarify, that as always that I am not an absolute authority on LOTR rules and rulings. I make my rulings based on the rules documents, the cards, and when needed my best judgement. Whatever I say here is my opinion and how I would rule the situation in a tournament, but if Decipher later decides to change (or clarify) the rules differently, please don&#39;t think less of me. (=<br />
<br />
So here goes...<br />
<br />
Because of the rules of the game, both side&#39;s Fellowships cannot be active at the same time. Only one side is active at any given time (either the Fellowship of the player on turn or the Shadow of the player not on turn). So during my opponent&#39;s turn, my fellowship cards (like Aggression) are not active and would not provide a damage bonus to my dwarves. However, my Ring-bearer is not active either. So the burdens on my Ring-bearer are not active and I cannot become corrupted because I have 5 burdens on Gimli (during my opponent&#39;s turn!). So to answer your first set of questions, no the other cards are not active, but because your Ring-bearer isn&#39;t either it&#39;s not a problem.<br />
<br />
The tricky part is when we determine tie breaks for a timed game. Normally, when time is called we compare the resistance of the two Ring-bearers. As I mentioned above, the Fellowship&#39;s of both sides cannot be active at the same time. So this is obviously a deviation from that rule. So for the purposes of determining resistance both Fellowships can be active at the same time. So alternate Ring-bearers who get a higher resistance from other Fellowship cards would get the benefits of those other cards being active.<br />
<br />
This however does not answer all questions. What about the Shadow cards, are they active also? What about initiative? If it&#39;s the start of the Regroup phase, it is possible for a player to have less then 4 cards in their hand. This is less of a concern for the current player on turn as it is for the Shadow player who played cards during their opponent&#39;s turn and may lose initiative because of it. These are answers only Decipher and DGMA can provide. Until then, it&#39;s up to the judgement of the judges in these situations.<br />
<br />
This is how I would rule it. For the purposes of determining Tie Breaks for a timed gamed...<br />
<br />
1. Both Fellowships are active.<br />
  - The precident is already set from previous Frodo/Frodo games.<br />
2. Shadow cards are not active. <br />
  - There is no precident for Shadow cards being considered for tie break determination.<br />
3. Both players have iniative<br />
  - Provided there are enough cards still remaining in their draw deck.<br />
<br />
#3 is based soley on my judgement and what I consider to be fair to both players. <br />
<br />
As I mentioned above, until this is clarified by Decipher or DGMA it&#39;s up to judges to make the decisions that are most fair to the players. That does not mean that other judges will do the same everywhere, and certain not every judge will do as I plan to do (and mentioned above). Sorry if I didn&#39;t fully answer your question.<br />
<br />
- Enrique <br></font><BR><font class="bfont"> <A HREF='/lotr/articles/articles.php?id=5670&view=1&PHPSESSID=c7fd488171dcc9f20d438c7ec38b96d2'>Read the Reviews</a><font class="bfont"> | <A HREF='/lotr/articles/articles.php?PHPSESSID=c7fd488171dcc9f20d438c7ec38b96d2'>Back to List</A></font><p><font class="bfont"> <b>You must be a member to contribute to Decktech.</b>  <p>Please <a href='/lotr/main/join.php?PHPSESSID=c7fd488171dcc9f20d438c7ec38b96d2'> become a registered member</a></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
